verbose_text: Real-time RT-PCR results showed that the at 24 hpi, mRNA levels of CASP8, DDX58 (also known as RIG-I), eIF4a1, HSP27, IFIH1 (also known as MDA5), IFIT3, ISG20, OAS1, RSAD2 (also known as viperin), and STAT1 were increased by 3.44-, 3.45-, 2.72-, 1.83-, 2.53-, 4.06-, 5.12-, 2.03-, 9.06-, and 1.67-fold, respectively, and by 3.03-, 6.36 -,3.16 -,4.03-, 7.02-, 3.80-, 4.23-, 2.91-, 10.67- and 2.33-fold, respectively, at 48 hpi, consistent with iTRAQ labeled LC-MS/MS data.
